{"lemma":"كَأْس","slug":"كَأْس","root":"ك.#.س","root_slug":"ك-_-س","root_link":"/words/roots/ك-_-س","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"كَأْس","root":"كأس","pos":"N","occurrence_count":6},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n36507","n37378","n37396","n37380","n43038"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%83%D9%8E%D8%A3%D9%92%D8%B3"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be clever, to be acute in intellect, to have a sharp mind"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to overcome in intellect, to surpass in shrewdness"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to walk with one foot less; to coil oneself up"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to prostrate, to cut down the standing firmly of, to throw head over heels"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to beat down, to abate the price offered by in haggling with","tags":["figuratively"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n36507","headword_ar":"كَاْسٌ","root":"kA^s","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (ISk, S, A, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAsN","text_ar":"كَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"suppressed, is allowable, (Msb,) and sometimes occurs, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A drinking-cup:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K:) or ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cup of wine;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cup containing wine;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cup full of wine:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) when not containing wine, it is not thus called; (IAar, S, Msb;) being in this case called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qadaHN","text_ar":"قَدَحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or it has the first and the second of these significations: (TA:) or it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wine itself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, AHát, Ibn-'Abbád:) or has this signification also: (K:) and is of the fem. gender: (S, A, Msb, K:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akow^usN","text_ar":"اَكْوُسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuw^uwsN","text_ar":"كُوُوسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiy^aAsN","text_ar":"كِيَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) the last with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA, [but written without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the CK,]) and, accord. to AHn,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiyaAsN","text_ar":"كِيَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", which, if correct, is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiwaAsN","text_ar":"كِوَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAsN","text_ar":"كَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"as representing"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2582},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAsaAtN","text_ar":"كَاسَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) It is used metaphorically in relation to every kind of disagreeable, hateful, or evil, things. Thus you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saqaAhu kaA^osFA mina Al*~ul~i","text_ar":"سَقَاهُ كَاْسًا مِنَ الذُّلِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He gave him to drink a cup of abasement"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina Alfuroqapi","text_ar":"مِنَ الفُرْقَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of separation"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina Almawoti","text_ar":"مِنَ المَوْتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of death"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina","text_ar":"مِنَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHub~i","text_ar":"الحُبِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of love"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saqaAhu","text_ar":"سَقَاهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlkaA^osa AlA^amar~a","text_ar":"الكَاْسَ الاَمَرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He gave him to drink the most bitter cup"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"death:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuw^uwsa AlmanaAyaA","text_ar":"كُوُوسَ المَنَايَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The cups of death;"},{"kind":"text","text":"lit.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deaths"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) Az. thinks that it may be derived from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaASa fulaAnN mina AlT~aEaAmi waAl$~araAbi","text_ar":"كَاصَ فُلَانٌ مِنَ الطَّعَامِ وَالشَّرَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning, “ Such a one ate and drank much ”; because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"S","text_ar":"ص"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"s","text_ar":"س"},{"kind":"text","text":"are interchangeable in many words on account of the nearness of their places of utterance. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["ISk","S","A","Msb","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n37378","headword_ar":"كَاسَ","root":"kws","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yakuwsu","text_ar":"يَكُوسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kawosN","text_ar":"كَوْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a camel)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"walked upon three legs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being hamstrung:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"raised one of his legs, and jumped upon the rest."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) Thus you say of a quadruped: but when said of another, it means,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went upon one leg."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAsa","text_ar":"كَاسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, TA,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yakuwsu","text_ar":"يَكُوسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kawosN","text_ar":"كَوْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became turned upside down,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"head downwards;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tkw~s","text_ar":"تكوّس","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a poor man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fell upon his head."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, * TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAsa fulaAnFA","text_ar":"كَاسَ فُلَانًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yakuwsuhu","text_ar":"يَكُوسُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kawosN","text_ar":"كَوْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He prostrated such a one;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AkAshu","text_ar":"اكاسهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ikaAsapN","text_ar":"اـِكَاسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) which latter verb is the more chaste: (Sgh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he threw him down upon his head;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kw~shu","text_ar":"كوّسهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or this last, which is said of God, (S, A, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"takowiysN","text_ar":"تَكْوِيسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He turned him upside down,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"head downwards,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon his head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Aln~aAri","text_ar":"فِى النَّارِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the fire"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of Hell]: (S, A:) and you say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY raA^osihi","text_ar":"عَلَى رَاْسِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaw~asotuhu","text_ar":"كَوَّسْتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I turned him over upon his head."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA","A","Sgh"]},{"entry_id":"n37396","headword_ar":"كَاسَ","root":"kys","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yakiysu","text_ar":"يَكِيسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kayosN","text_ar":"كَيْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiyaAsapN","text_ar":"كِيَاسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuwsaY","text_ar":"كُوسَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"put in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":", [originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuyosaY","text_ar":"كُيْسَى"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (Seer [mentioned by him as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kayosN","text_ar":"كَيْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a boy, S [but often said of a man also,])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, acute,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharp,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quick, in intellect; shrewd; clever; ingenious; skilful; knowing; intelligent:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kayosN","text_ar":"كَيْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HumoqN","text_ar":"حُمْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, A, K;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZarofN","text_ar":"ظَرْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiq~apN","text_ar":"خِقَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tawaq~udN","text_ar":"تَوَقُّدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiTonapN","text_ar":"فِطْنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiqohN","text_ar":"فِقْهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqolN","text_ar":"عَقْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAar, A, Msb, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAsa fiY AlA^amori","text_ar":"كَاسَ فِى الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yakiysu","text_ar":"يَكِيسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kayosN","text_ar":"كَيْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mgh, TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tky~s","text_ar":"تكيّس","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tkAys","text_ar":"تكايس","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He acted gently,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with good gentleness"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moderation"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"calmness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAsahu","text_ar":"كَاسَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yakiysuhu","text_ar":"يَكِيسُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, * K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kayosN","text_ar":"كَيْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He overcame him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"surpassed him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiyaAsap","text_ar":"كِيَاسَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kayos","text_ar":"كَيْس"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Nh) [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acuteness"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharpness"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quickness of intellect;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: see above]. So in the following words of a trad., (K,) said by the prophet to Jábir Ibn-'Abd-Allah El-Ansáree, (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ataraAniY","text_ar":"اَتَرَانِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~amaA kisotuka liA=xu*a jamalaka laka Alv~amanu walaka Aljamalu","text_ar":"اـِنَّمَا كِسْتُكَ لِا=خُذَ جَمَلَكَ لَكَ الثَّمَنُ وَلَكَ الجَمَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dost thou think me to have only overcome thee in acuteness"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharpness"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quickness of intellect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in order that I might take thy camel? Thine be the price, and thine be the camel"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K, * TA:) or, according to another relation,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xu*o","text_ar":"خُذْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jamalaka wamaAlaka","text_ar":"جَمَلَكَ وَمَالَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Take thou thy camel and thy property"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and accord. to another,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~amaA maA kasotuka","text_ar":"اـِنَّمَا مَا كَسْتُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that I have only acted in a niggardly manner with thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"], from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmikaAsu","text_ar":"المِكَاسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kayisa","text_ar":"كَيِسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yakoyasu","text_ar":"يَكْيَسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kayasN","text_ar":"كَيَسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is also mentioned by IKtt as a dial. form of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAsa","text_ar":"كَاسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He overcame"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"surpassed"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in acuteness"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.] (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","TA","A","Mgh","K","Nh"]},{"entry_id":"n37380","headword_ar":"كَاسٌ","root":"kws","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaA^osN","text_ar":"كَاْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n43038","headword_ar":"كَاسٍ","root":"ksw","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having clothing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rub~a","text_ar":"رُبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}